WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.759 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:13.759 --> 00:00:15.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hello and welcome.

00:00:15.050 --> 00:00:16.230 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:18.450 align:middle line:84%
After you see the images
that you are about to see

00:00:18.450 --> 00:00:20.950 align:middle line:84%
and you hear the concepts
that are revealed,

00:00:20.950 --> 00:00:23.200 align:middle line:84%
you will look at
life differently.

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:26.340 align:middle line:84%
I absolutely did, and that's
exactly what happened to me.

00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:28.816 align:middle line:84%
The question is what are
you willing to do about it?

00:00:28.816 --> 00:00:30.440 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're
discussing today.

00:00:30.440 --> 00:00:33.550 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking about a very
unconventional documentary

00:00:33.550 --> 00:00:37.210 align:middle line:84%
called "THRIVE," and
it's both educational

00:00:37.210 --> 00:00:39.100 align:middle line:90%
and very inspirational.

00:00:39.100 --> 00:00:42.140 align:middle line:84%
And joining me are the
filmmakers Foster Gamble

00:00:42.140 --> 00:00:43.750 align:middle line:90%
and Kimberly Carter Gamble.

00:00:43.750 --> 00:00:46.830 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for joining me,
and thank you for the film.

00:00:46.830 --> 00:00:48.310 align:middle line:90%
Really, thank you for the film.

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:48.960 align:middle line:90%
I mean that.

00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:51.080 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing what
you've put into it.

00:00:51.080 --> 00:00:53.255 align:middle line:84%
How long did it take
you to make this film?

00:00:53.255 --> 00:00:55.564 align:middle line:84%
>>FOSTER GAMBLE: I'll let
the producer go for that.

00:00:55.564 --> 00:00:57.980 align:middle line:84%
>>KIMBERLY CARTER GAMBLE: It
too us eight years, actually.

00:00:57.980 --> 00:00:59.620 align:middle line:84%
It took us eight
years to put together,

00:00:59.620 --> 00:01:02.080 align:middle line:84%
the website and the
film, because they really

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:03.540 align:middle line:90%
do go together.

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:05.385 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: One of the
greatest aspects,

00:01:05.385 --> 00:01:09.000 align:middle line:84%
and I think is a guest in
itself, is the graphics.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:10.382 align:middle line:90%
The graphics are phenomenal.

00:01:10.382 --> 00:01:11.840 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
be showing clips

00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:13.381 align:middle line:84%
throughout the entire
show, so you're

00:01:13.381 --> 00:01:15.360 align:middle line:84%
going to be able to
see this, but that

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:17.670 align:middle line:84%
must have taken teams
to put together.

00:01:17.670 --> 00:01:21.662 align:middle line:84%
And how much-- how many
teams did you have on this?

00:01:21.662 --> 00:01:24.060 align:middle line:84%
>>GAMBLE: Well, we had a
wonderful special effects

00:01:24.060 --> 00:01:27.080 align:middle line:84%
team from Ashland, Oregon,
called Liquid Buddha Studios.

00:01:27.080 --> 00:01:29.870 align:middle line:84%
Goa Lobaugh and
his team up there.

00:01:29.870 --> 00:01:32.750 align:middle line:84%
And they were the primary ones
for the 3D computer graphics.

00:01:32.750 --> 00:01:34.541 align:middle line:84%
And then we had some
other people, as well,

00:01:34.541 --> 00:01:36.541 align:middle line:84%
doing some of the 2D
animations that you'll see.

00:01:36.541 --> 00:01:38.582 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's really a
combination of visionaries,

00:01:38.582 --> 00:01:40.050 align:middle line:84%
though, that you
needed to put this

00:01:40.050 --> 00:01:43.290 align:middle line:84%
together, between the visuals
and your concepts and so forth.

00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:46.080 align:middle line:84%
So how long-- first of
all, the movie "THRIVE"

00:01:46.080 --> 00:01:48.090 align:middle line:84%
is about, in a nutshell,
if you could give it

00:01:48.090 --> 00:01:50.048 align:middle line:84%
to me in a nutshell--
we're going to see clips,

00:01:50.048 --> 00:01:51.170 align:middle line:90%
but what is it about?

00:01:51.170 --> 00:01:54.070 align:middle line:84%
>>GAMBLE: The title is "THRIVE,
What on Earth Will it Take?"

00:01:54.070 --> 00:01:58.110 align:middle line:84%
And it's really an exploration
into what is in the way

00:01:58.110 --> 00:02:01.840 align:middle line:84%
of human beings' and our
planet's natural drive

00:02:01.840 --> 00:02:03.310 align:middle line:90%
to thrive.

00:02:03.310 --> 00:02:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And if we could figure
out what's in the way,

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:08.340 align:middle line:84%
then we get a handle on how
to eliminate that and let

00:02:08.340 --> 00:02:09.880 align:middle line:84%
that natural life
impulse come out.

00:02:09.880 --> 00:02:13.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What caused you to ask
those questions in your life?

00:02:13.870 --> 00:02:17.140 align:middle line:84%
>>GAMBLE: Well, for me,
from a very young age, when

00:02:17.140 --> 00:02:18.730 align:middle line:90%
I look back, I was a peacemaker.

00:02:18.730 --> 00:02:20.810 align:middle line:84%
I was breaking up fights
in elementary school

00:02:20.810 --> 00:02:23.730 align:middle line:84%
and I could see how people
weren't communicating, weren't

00:02:23.730 --> 00:02:25.430 align:middle line:84%
understanding each
other, and so forth.

00:02:25.430 --> 00:02:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And as that grew
over time, I realized

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:31.380 align:middle line:84%
that the media was a
really powerful tool

00:02:31.380 --> 00:02:37.520 align:middle line:84%
for not only informing
people, but also having people

00:02:37.520 --> 00:02:39.705 align:middle line:84%
see each other's points
of view and resolving

00:02:39.705 --> 00:02:41.080 align:middle line:84%
the conflicts that
really have us

00:02:41.080 --> 00:02:44.290 align:middle line:84%
at the threat of
annihilating life

00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:45.730 align:middle line:90%
as we know it on the planet.

00:02:45.730 --> 00:02:47.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you have
been a peacemaker

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:49.740 align:middle line:84%
in your previous
professions as well where

00:02:49.740 --> 00:02:51.990 align:middle line:84%
you were a mediator,
was that what--?

00:02:51.990 --> 00:02:54.834 align:middle line:84%
>>GAMBLE: I taught communication
and conflict resolution,

00:02:54.834 --> 00:02:57.250 align:middle line:84%
and worked with companies in
Silicon Valley for many years

00:02:57.250 --> 00:02:58.230 align:middle line:90%
doing that.

00:02:58.230 --> 00:03:01.200 align:middle line:84%
And prior to that I taught
the non-violent martial art

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:02.560 align:middle line:90%
of aikido for 15 years.

00:03:02.560 --> 00:03:05.820 align:middle line:84%
So, the latter work was
really an application

00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:07.869 align:middle line:84%
in interpersonal--
where the battles really

00:03:07.869 --> 00:03:09.910 align:middle line:84%
take place of what I've
been studying on the mat.

00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:10.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Isn't it
amazing when you

00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:12.890 align:middle line:84%
have a purpose on this
planet that you're here

00:03:12.890 --> 00:03:15.420 align:middle line:84%
to do, you can't do anything
other than fulfill it?

00:03:15.420 --> 00:03:17.799 align:middle line:84%
When it's really
that true purpose.

00:03:17.799 --> 00:03:19.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CARTER GAMBLE:
And when it's clear.

00:03:19.340 --> 00:03:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And getting clear about that
is a big part of the task.

00:03:21.760 --> 00:03:24.730 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I think a
big part of our intention

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:28.510 align:middle line:84%
behind "THRIVE" was
to kind of unpack

00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:31.820 align:middle line:84%
a combination of two things
that have been really

00:03:31.820 --> 00:03:33.570 align:middle line:84%
important in my
life, having to do

00:03:33.570 --> 00:03:36.570 align:middle line:84%
with the combination
of passionate intent

00:03:36.570 --> 00:03:38.570 align:middle line:90%
and unconflicted behavior.

00:03:38.570 --> 00:03:41.664 align:middle line:84%
Because what I have found
is that passionate intent

00:03:41.664 --> 00:03:43.080 align:middle line:84%
is actually a lot
easier to muster

00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:46.490 align:middle line:90%
than unconflicted behavior.

00:03:46.490 --> 00:03:51.330 align:middle line:84%
So for us, the motivation and
the process of making "THRIVE"

00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:55.130 align:middle line:84%
was really how can-- There
are so many people who care

00:03:55.130 --> 00:03:57.260 align:middle line:84%
and who are working
in one way or another

00:03:57.260 --> 00:03:59.162 align:middle line:84%
to help solve the
problems on this planet.

00:03:59.162 --> 00:03:59.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Millions.

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:01.890 align:middle line:84%
>>CARTER GAMBLE: Millions
of people are working,

00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:05.570 align:middle line:84%
and yet, things have been
continuing to get worse.

00:04:05.570 --> 00:04:08.730 align:middle line:84%
And so, for me, it was
looking at how can we

00:04:08.730 --> 00:04:12.460 align:middle line:84%
help clarify-- I'll give an
example of conflicted behavior

00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:14.600 align:middle line:84%
in my own life that sort
of led to this, which was,

00:04:14.600 --> 00:04:17.640 align:middle line:84%
when I was in college I
was working to stop coal

00:04:17.640 --> 00:04:21.410 align:middle line:84%
and nuclear power projects,
which I thought were dangerous.

00:04:21.410 --> 00:04:24.830 align:middle line:84%
So, my ritual was that
I would finish work

00:04:24.830 --> 00:04:27.390 align:middle line:84%
on Fridays-- we'd have
meetings every other week--

00:04:27.390 --> 00:04:31.260 align:middle line:84%
I would drive to the meeting
across town from my house.

00:04:31.260 --> 00:04:34.870 align:middle line:84%
And I would, on my way,
stop at Bank of America

00:04:34.870 --> 00:04:36.490 align:middle line:90%
and deposit my paycheck.

00:04:36.490 --> 00:04:38.710 align:middle line:90%
Then I would go to the meeting.

00:04:38.710 --> 00:04:41.060 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't
understand at the time

00:04:41.060 --> 00:04:44.130 align:middle line:84%
that banks use their
customers' deposits

00:04:44.130 --> 00:04:47.160 align:middle line:84%
to make loans to corporations
so that the corporations can

00:04:47.160 --> 00:04:48.324 align:middle line:90%
fund their projects.

00:04:48.324 --> 00:04:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I don't think
most of us realize that.

00:04:50.240 --> 00:04:52.198 align:middle line:84%
>>CARTER GAMBLE: Well,
in fact, Bank of America

00:04:52.198 --> 00:04:55.620 align:middle line:84%
was using my deposits to fund
the exact same corporations

00:04:55.620 --> 00:04:58.760 align:middle line:84%
that I was, otherwise
then, trying to stop.

00:04:58.760 --> 00:05:01.090 align:middle line:90%
So that's conflicted behavior.

00:05:01.090 --> 00:05:04.605 align:middle line:84%
And we had an opportunity
to do the study

00:05:04.605 --> 00:05:05.880 align:middle line:90%
and kind of get into it.

00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:08.600 align:middle line:84%
And so a big part of the
intention for "THRIVE"

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.680 align:middle line:84%
is that, on the website
and in the movie,

00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:13.090 align:middle line:84%
it's to help us
understand how can we

00:05:13.090 --> 00:05:16.250 align:middle line:84%
align our passionate
intent, which so many have,

00:05:16.250 --> 00:05:18.700 align:middle line:84%
with unconflicted behavior
so that we actually

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:20.380 align:middle line:84%
get the results that
we're aiming for.

00:05:20.380 --> 00:05:22.046 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it's
definitely not designed

00:05:22.046 --> 00:05:23.759 align:middle line:84%
for us to understand
that at all.

00:05:23.759 --> 00:05:25.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's what the beauty
is about your film, is

00:05:25.800 --> 00:05:28.260 align:middle line:84%
it really clearly
and graphically,

00:05:28.260 --> 00:05:32.380 align:middle line:84%
it explains and illustrates
how the connections are all

00:05:32.380 --> 00:05:35.830 align:middle line:84%
led around the control
of an elite few.

00:05:35.830 --> 00:05:38.950 align:middle line:84%
And we've heard about
the 99% versus the 1,

00:05:38.950 --> 00:05:41.090 align:middle line:84%
but this really
explains it in detail,

00:05:41.090 --> 00:05:43.260 align:middle line:84%
which is-- I'm very,
very grateful for.

00:05:43.260 --> 00:05:46.184 align:middle line:84%
And before you did this
movie, you were a journalist?

00:05:46.184 --> 00:05:47.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CARTER GAMBLE: Yes, I was.

00:05:47.350 --> 00:05:47.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great.

00:05:47.890 --> 00:05:48.806 align:middle line:90%
>>CARTER GAMBLE: Yeah.

00:05:48.806 --> 00:05:51.380 align:middle line:84%
I think-- I mean, everything
that I've ever done,

00:05:51.380 --> 00:05:55.450 align:middle line:84%
I think, led to what I brought
to bear it in "THRIVE."

00:05:55.450 --> 00:05:59.970 align:middle line:84%
In particular, I think
the tone of the movie,

00:05:59.970 --> 00:06:03.300 align:middle line:84%
and knowing that we really
wanted to focus on solutions,

00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:06.870 align:middle line:84%
and that we also really
wanted the website

00:06:06.870 --> 00:06:09.140 align:middle line:84%
to be there as a
tool for people to do

00:06:09.140 --> 00:06:11.110 align:middle line:90%
their own further exploration.

00:06:11.110 --> 00:06:12.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is so
well thought out.

00:06:12.770 --> 00:06:15.530 align:middle line:84%
And I appreciate you saying that
because I see a lot of DVDs,

00:06:15.530 --> 00:06:20.160 align:middle line:84%
and there are-- 99% of the
DVD is problem and pain.

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:23.040 align:middle line:84%
And I look throughout the
whole DVD for the solution,

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:26.560 align:middle line:84%
and there's, maybe, the last
10 minutes as an afterthought.

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:29.960 align:middle line:84%
And you focus the entire
second half on solutions

00:06:29.960 --> 00:06:31.350 align:middle line:90%
because that's what we need.

00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:34.292 align:middle line:84%
So, first of all, most
of it is about awareness.

00:06:34.292 --> 00:06:35.750 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look
at the clip here.

00:06:35.750 --> 00:06:38.380 align:middle line:84%
This is a kind of an overview
of the movie and how it got

00:06:38.380 --> 00:06:38.880 align:middle line:90%
started.

00:06:38.880 --> 00:06:40.600 align:middle line:84%
There are some
images in here that

00:06:40.600 --> 00:06:42.200 align:middle line:90%
are hard hitting but important.

00:06:42.200 --> 00:06:43.654 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:06:43.654 --> 00:06:44.320 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:48.040 align:middle line:84%
-Consider what is surely one
of the greatest wonders of all,

00:06:48.040 --> 00:06:52.680 align:middle line:84%
how a tiny egg and a single,
irrepressibly plucky sperm

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:55.000 align:middle line:84%
can unleash a process
that brings forth,

00:06:55.000 --> 00:07:01.040 align:middle line:84%
in the end, another one of
us, a being of vast ability

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:05.760 align:middle line:84%
and unlimited potential with
a brain capable of complex

00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:11.710 align:middle line:84%
and soaring self-reflection,
legs made to dance and run,

00:07:11.710 --> 00:07:15.200 align:middle line:84%
fingers nimble enough
to weave a basket,

00:07:15.200 --> 00:07:19.300 align:middle line:90%
play a violin, caress a face.

00:07:19.300 --> 00:07:21.690 align:middle line:84%
If nature teaches
us anything, it

00:07:21.690 --> 00:07:25.440 align:middle line:84%
is that life is meant to work,
and that like every living

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:29.176 align:middle line:90%
thing, our purpose is to thrive.

00:07:29.176 --> 00:07:36.080 align:middle line:90%
[BABY CRYING]

00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:38.940 align:middle line:84%
-And yet, for the majority
of people on the planet,

00:07:38.940 --> 00:07:43.070 align:middle line:84%
life is not about thriving;
it's about surviving,

00:07:43.070 --> 00:07:46.750 align:middle line:90%
just trying to hang on.

00:07:46.750 --> 00:07:49.920 align:middle line:84%
Is this really the
best we can do?

00:07:49.920 --> 00:07:54.610 align:middle line:84%
Did the universe labor for
nearly 14 billion years only to

00:07:54.610 --> 00:07:56.560 align:middle line:84%
bring forth a species
that would end up

00:07:56.560 --> 00:08:00.760 align:middle line:84%
as an enemy to life itself
and to its own home?

00:08:00.760 --> 00:08:02.550 align:middle line:90%
I don't think so.

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:06.660 align:middle line:84%
My name is Foster Gamble, and
I have spent nearly a lifetime

00:08:06.660 --> 00:08:08.970 align:middle line:84%
trying to figure
out what happened.

00:08:08.970 --> 00:08:10.850 align:middle line:84%
What is happening
that could account

00:08:10.850 --> 00:08:15.270 align:middle line:84%
for the staggering agony and
deprivation on this planet?

00:08:15.270 --> 00:08:18.190 align:middle line:84%
As a young man,
driven by the misery

00:08:18.190 --> 00:08:21.220 align:middle line:84%
I saw and by my fear
for our survival,

00:08:21.220 --> 00:08:24.920 align:middle line:84%
I set out on a journey
seeking to answer questions

00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:28.940 align:middle line:84%
like is it even possible
for humans to thrive?

00:08:28.940 --> 00:08:32.870 align:middle line:90%
If so, why aren't we?

00:08:32.870 --> 00:08:36.510 align:middle line:84%
My research led me to places
I never expected to go,

00:08:36.510 --> 00:08:40.659 align:middle line:84%
revealing surprising discoveries
that seemed unrelated at first,

00:08:40.659 --> 00:08:43.080 align:middle line:84%
but which turned out to
be crucially connected,

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:44.490 align:middle line:90%
as you'll see.

00:08:44.490 --> 00:08:47.340 align:middle line:84%
I found a code, a
pattern in nature

00:08:47.340 --> 00:08:52.200 align:middle line:84%
that's been embedded in arts and
icons throughout the centuries.

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:54.390 align:middle line:84%
I believe this
code holds the key

00:08:54.390 --> 00:08:58.130 align:middle line:84%
to a new source of clean,
sustainable energy that

00:08:58.130 --> 00:09:02.080 align:middle line:84%
could completely revolutionize
the way all people live.

00:09:02.080 --> 00:09:05.330 align:middle line:84%
I came to understand how our
economic system is rigged.

00:09:05.330 --> 00:09:09.730 align:middle line:84%
And I found out what
we can do about it.

00:09:09.730 --> 00:09:12.450 align:middle line:84%
My journey revealed ways
we can claim our power

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:18.520 align:middle line:84%
to create liberating, healthy
systems everywhere on earth.

00:09:18.520 --> 00:09:21.820 align:middle line:84%
I have realized that
we are not a mistake.

00:09:21.820 --> 00:09:24.180 align:middle line:90%
We are simply mistaken.

00:09:24.180 --> 00:09:27.110 align:middle line:84%
We've been blinded
to our brilliance,

00:09:27.110 --> 00:09:30.910 align:middle line:84%
shorn of our strength,
ignorant of our genius,

00:09:30.910 --> 00:09:36.050 align:middle line:84%
unaware of our true
power and magnificence.

00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:38.730 align:middle line:90%
But all that is about to change.

00:09:38.730 --> 00:09:40.430 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

